1. Install Docker
	i.  Install .deb file of docker (For Ubuntu)
	ii. sudo dpkg -i /path_to_deb_file

Steps to enable docker to run without sudo:
	i. sudo groupadd docker
	ii. sudo usermod -aG docker $USER  
	iii. Logout and again login.

Build Docker Image:
Go to ONLINE_JUDGE directory and type:
	docker build -t judge_image .


Docker commands:
1. To build docker image: sudo docker build -t ubuntu .
2. To list docker images: sudo docker images
3. To delete docker image: sudo docker rmi -f <image_id>

To uninstall docker:
1. sudo apt-get purge docker-ce
2. sudo rm -rf /var/lib/docker